          </p>
          <p>
            Using the bootstrap: <br />
          </p>
          <p>
            <b>1. Copy & paste way:</b><br />
          </p>
          <p>
            a) Close Blackcoin wallet. (if it is running)<br />
          </p>
          <p>
            b) Place file into the Blackcoin data directory. The default location of data directory is as
            follow:<br />
          </p>
          <p>
            %AppData%\Roaming\Blackcoin\ for windows<br />
            ~/Library/App Support/Blackcoin/ for mac<br />
            ~/.blackcoin/ for linux<br />
          </p>
          <p>
            c) Open Blackcoin wallet.<br />
          </p>
          <p>
            d) Wait for Blackcoin wallet to open while it rescans the bootstrap and unpacks it. (may take long time
            depends on your computer)<br />
          </p>
          <p>
            <b>2. Command line way:</b><br />
          </p>
          <p>
            a) Start the client with the <span>loadblock method:</span><br />
          </p>
          <p>
            <span>Windows:</span> blackcoin-qt.exe -loadblock=C:\..\bootstrap.dat<br />
            <span>Linux:</span> ./blackcoin-qt -loadblock=/home/../bootstrap.dat<br />
          </p>
          <p>
            b) In bottom left of the wallet, it will say "Importing blocks..."
          </p>
